snippet.textOriginal: Very nicely explained, thank you for this!

snippet.textDisplay:
@Knowable Magazine The thing I find odd is no one is discussing or alarmed about its odd mutation rate, given the base viruses genome and it mutation rate is lower than influenza.

I suspect it may have to do with its evolutionary path, it's mutation by interacting with other corona viruses.

Since it's Zoonotic shift it has a plethora of new corona viruses to interact with in humans.

I am glad the last words in the video emphasise the reason in reducing infections being to limit its opportunities to mutate. Something I wish was expressed in the news more.
